  "local_port": 49508,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "If you want to delete your Gmail account only from one device while retaining it on other devices, follow these steps:\n\n### For Android Devices:\n1. **Open the Settings app** on your Android device.\n2. Scroll down and tap on **Accounts**.\n3. Find and select **Google**.\n4. Choose the **Google account** you want to remove.\n5. Tap on **Remove Account**.\n   - Confirm the removal if prompted.\n\n### For iOS Devices (iPhone/iPad):\n1. Open the **Settings app**.\n2. Scroll down and tap on **Passwords & Accounts** (sometimes listed as Mail, Contacts, Calendar, depending on iOS version).\n3. Select the **Gmail account** you want to remove.\n4. Tap **Delete Account**.\n   - Confirm the removal if prompted.\n\n### For Windows Devices:\n1. Open the **Settings app**.\n2. Click on **Accounts**.\n3. Select **Email & accounts**.\n4. Find the **Gmail account** under 'Accounts used by other apps.'\n5. Click on it and select **Manage**.\n6. Choose the option to **delete or remove the account**.\n\n### For macOS Devices:\n1. Open **System Preferences**.\n2. Click on **Internet Accounts**.\n3. Select the **Google account** you want to remove.\n4. Click on the **minus (-)** button to remove the account.\n\nBy following these steps, you will only remove the Gmail account from the specific device you are working on. The Gmail account will remain active and accessible on other devices and through the web interface.",
